          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"what-is-a-buffer\">What is a BUFFER ?</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">A buffer is a temporary storage area that holds transient (inflight) data in memory.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">It is a chunk of contiguous memory that allows processes compesate for differences in processing speed.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Using buffers, you can reduce slow operations and facilitate async comms between processes.</span></span>"
          }
